kind.prompt:
You are working in /tmp/sv-ba8d5996e1814909ad84c4a59c7a32c4/ShipmentTracker — a Blazor Web App solution with Interactive Auto global mode and Individual authentication. The solution has two projects:
- `ShipmentTracker` (server) 
- `ShipmentTracker.Client` (WebAssembly client)

The app is for a logistics company tracking shipments. Requirements:
- Dispatchers view a list of shipments with status and destination
- Customers check their shipment status and estimated delivery
- Authentication with roles (Dispatcher, Customer)

## Architecture (Auto mode)

In Auto mode, interactive components live in `.Client` project. They cannot access DbContext directly. Pattern:
1. Define interface in `.Client` project
2. Client implementation uses HttpClient to call server APIs
3. Server implementation uses DbContext directly  
4. Both Program.cs files register the appropriate implementation
5. Server exposes minimal API endpoints

## Tasks

### 1. Create shared models in `.Client` project

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Models/Shipment.cs`:
```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

public class Shipment
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string TrackingNumber { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Origin { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Destination { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public ShipmentStatus Status { get; set; }
    public DateTime CreatedDate { get; set; }
    public DateTime? EstimatedDelivery { get; set; }
    public string CustomerEmail { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Description { get; set; } = string.Empty;
}

public enum ShipmentStatus
{
    Pending,
    PickedUp,
    InTransit,
    OutForDelivery,
    Delivered,
    Exception
}
```

### 2. Create service interface in `.Client` project

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Services/IShipmentService.cs`:
```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

public interface IShipmentService
{
    Task<List<Shipment>> GetAllShipmentsAsync();
    Task<List<Shipment>> GetShipmentsForCustomerAsync();
    Task<Shipment?> GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber);
    Task UpdateShipmentStatusAsync(int id, ShipmentStatus status);
}
```

### 3. Create client-side implementation using HttpClient

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Services/ShipmentServiceClient.cs`:
```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

using System.Net.Http.Json;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

public class ShipmentServiceClient(HttpClient http) : IShipmentService
{
    public async Task<List<Shipment>> GetAllShipmentsAsync()
    {
        return await http.GetFromJsonAsync<List<Shipment>>("api/shipments") ?? [];
    }

    public async Task<List<Shipment>> GetShipmentsForCustomerAsync()
    {
        return await http.GetFromJsonAsync<List<Shipment>>("api/shipments/mine") ?? [];
    }

    public async Task<Shipment?> GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber)
    {
        return await http.GetFromJsonAsync<Shipment?>($"api/shipments/track/{trackingNumber}");
    }

    public async Task UpdateShipmentStatusAsync(int id, ShipmentStatus status)
    {
        await http.PutAsJsonAsync($"api/shipments/{id}/status", status);
    }
}
```

### 4. Register HttpClient and services in Client Program.cs

Edit `ShipmentTracker.Client/Program.cs` to add:
```csharp
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.WebAssembly.Hosting;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

var builder = WebAssemblyHostBuilder.CreateDefault(args);

builder.Services.AddAuthorizationCore();
builder.Services.AddCascadingAuthenticationState();
builder.Services.AddAuthenticationStateDeserialization();

builder.Services.AddHttpClient("ServerAPI", client =>
    client.BaseAddress = new Uri(builder.HostEnvironment.BaseAddress))
    .AddHttpMessageHandler<CookieHandler>();
builder.Services.AddScoped(sp => sp.GetRequiredService<IHttpClientFactory>().CreateClient("ServerAPI"));
builder.Services.AddScoped<IShipmentService, ShipmentServiceClient>();

await builder.Build().RunAsync();
```

Wait — actually in Blazor WASM with Auto mode and cookie auth, HttpClient should just use the base address directly. The auth cookie is sent automatically. Simplify:

```csharp
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.WebAssembly.Hosting;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

var builder = WebAssemblyHostBuilder.CreateDefault(args);

builder.Services.AddAuthorizationCore();
builder.Services.AddCascadingAuthenticationState();
builder.Services.AddAuthenticationStateDeserialization();

builder.Services.AddScoped(sp => new HttpClient { BaseAddress = new Uri(builder.HostEnvironment.BaseAddress) });
builder.Services.AddScoped<IShipmentService, ShipmentServiceClient>();

await builder.Build().RunAsync();
```

### 5. Add Shipment entity and seed data on the server

Edit `ShipmentTracker/Data/ApplicationDbContext.cs` to add a DbSet for Shipment and seed some data. The server project needs its own entity that maps to the DB. Create `ShipmentTracker/Data/ShipmentEntity.cs`:

```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Data;

public class ShipmentEntity
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string TrackingNumber { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Origin { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Destination { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public int Status { get; set; }
    public DateTime CreatedDate { get; set; }
    public DateTime? EstimatedDelivery { get; set; }
    public string CustomerEmail { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Description { get; set; } = string.Empty;
}
```

Add `DbSet<ShipmentEntity> Shipments` to ApplicationDbContext and override OnModelCreating to seed data.

### 6. Create server-side IShipmentService implementation

Create `ShipmentTracker/Services/ShipmentServiceServer.cs` that uses the DbContext.

### 7. Create API endpoints

In `ShipmentTracker/Program.cs`, add minimal API endpoints:
- `GET /api/shipments` — returns all shipments (requires Dispatcher role)
- `GET /api/shipments/mine` — returns shipments for authenticated customer
- `GET /api/shipments/track/{trackingNumber}` — returns shipment by tracking number (authenticated)
- `PUT /api/shipments/{id}/status` — update status (requires Dispatcher role)

### 8. Register server-side service in server Program.cs

Add `builder.Services.AddScoped<IShipmentService, ShipmentServiceServer>();` and add the reference to the Client project's services interface (already referenced since server references client project).

### 9. Create pages in `.Client` project

**Remove** Counter.razor and Weather.razor from `.Client/Pages/`.

**Update** `Home.razor` to be a simple landing page.

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Pages/DispatcherDashboard.razor`:
- @page "/dispatcher"
- @attribute [Authorize(Roles = "Dispatcher")]
- Shows table of all shipments with columns: Tracking #, Origin, Destination, Status, Est. Delivery
- Has a dropdown to filter by status
- Each row has a button/dropdown to update status

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Pages/TrackShipment.razor`:
- @page "/track"
- @attribute [Authorize]
- Shows a search box where customer can enter tracking number
- Displays shipment details with status timeline and estimated delivery
- Also shows a list of the customer's shipments

### 10. Update navigation

Edit `ShipmentTracker.Client/Layout/NavMenu.razor` to show appropriate links based on role:
- Dispatcher: Dashboard link
- All authenticated: Track Shipment link

### 11. Add roles and seed a dispatcher user

Add role seeding in Program.cs — create "Dispatcher" and "Customer" roles on startup.

### 12. Create an EF migration

Run `dotnet ef migrations add InitialCreate` in the server project (if dotnet-ef is available) or use `EnsureCreated` approach for development.

### 13. Create AGENTS.md

Create `ShipmentTracker/AGENTS.md` with the Auto global template content, replacing {AppName} with ShipmentTracker, and adding an Authentication section.

## Important notes:
- Do NOT add @rendermode to any pages — global mode handles it via App.razor
- Identity/Account pages must stay static SSR
- All interactive pages go in the .Client project
- Use `@using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models` and `@using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services` in _Imports.razor
- After all changes, run `dotnet build ShipmentTracker.sln` from the solution directory to verify everything compiles

